    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-02-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-02-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="184"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d184">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Rockhill</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>
                        </placeName>,<lb/>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-02-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 253.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch No. 499, of the 7th ultimo, in which you confirm your telegram of the
                    5th <pb facs="0330" n="218" xml:id="pg_218"/> ultimo, reporting the receipt by
                    the consul-general at Canton of the sum of $25,000 gold paid by the Chinese
                    Government as indemnity for the Lienchou massacre.</p>
                <p>The dispatch has been read with interest, and your course in the matter has been
                    approved by the department.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
